 ('74', '139', '3', '1', 'en_us', '26', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Agawam High School Athletic Facility Renovation \",\"slug\":\"agawam-high-school-athletic-facility-renovation\",\"postDate\":1498665240,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"132\":{\"name\":\"\",\"street\":\"\",\"street2\":\"\",\"city\":\"Agawam\",\"region\":\"Massachusetts \",\"postalCode\":\"\",\"country\":\"US\"},\"133\":\"Agawam High School \",\"3\":{\"240\":{\"type\":\"textPanel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"What we faced. \",\"body\":\"<p>A wonderfully passionate community was in dire need of safer and more adequate athletic facilities at their High School Athletic Complex. What existed was an outdated, unsafe, undersized, and unuseable track and bleacher system, non-accessible and inadequate restroom, concessions, and storage facilities. The inadequate number of tennis courts in need of repair and an overall inefficient and unsafe layout of conflicting field and sport uses.<\\/p>\"}},\"236\":{\"type\":\"multipleImagePanel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"leftImage\":[\"229\"],\"rightImage\":[\"230\"],\"upperImage\":\"right\",\"backgroundImageIsVisible\":\"\"}},\"143\":{\"type\":\"textPanel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Including Passionate Stakeholders in the Master Planning Process \",\"body\":\"<p>Although with every design project the actual details for construction are extremely important to the success of the project, &nbsp;perhaps equally important is the early involvement of the stakeholders in the concept stages of the project. &nbsp;&nbsp;Our goal of the masterplanning process was to engage with the Track Committee and the users of the facility, the coaches, the booster club, the players, and the maintenance and facilities staff. &nbsp;Only after having an informed ideas of what the stakeholders envision, could we put our designer hats on and begin the design and concept planning. &nbsp;By having p